covid_data_df['dateRep'] = pd.to_datetime(covid_data_df['dateRep'], format='%d/%m/%Y').dt.date

covid_dates = list(sorted(covid_data_df['dateRep'].unique()))
one_day = datetime.timedelta(days=1)

def autolabel(rects):
    """Attach a text label above each bar in *rects*, displaying its height."""
    for rect in rects:
        height = rect.get_height()
        ax.annotate('{}'.format(height),
        xy=(rect.get_x() + rect.get_width() / 2, height),
        xytext=(0, 0),
        textcoords="offset points",
        ha='center', va='bottom')

print('Most recent date in file: ', covid_data_df['dateRep'].max())

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 8))


x = np.arange(len(top_10_by_deaths['df_usa']['cases'].iloc[-30:]))

count = 0
for country in top_10_by_deaths:
    if count < 6:
        ax.plot(x, (top_10_by_deaths[country]['cases'].iloc[-30:] / top_10_by_deaths[country]['popData2018'].iloc[-30:]) * 100, label=top_10_by_deaths[country]['countriesAndTerritories'].iloc[0], linewidth=2)
    else:
        ax.plot(x, (top_10_by_deaths[country]['cases'].iloc[-30:] / top_10_by_deaths[country]['popData2018'].iloc[-30:]) * 100, label=top_10_by_deaths[country]['countriesAndTerritories'].iloc[0], linewidth=2, linestyle='dotted')
    count += 1

ax.set(ylabel="Percent of Population Infected", title="COVID-19 Cases\n(Percent of Population)")

ax.set_xticklabels(np.arange(min(covid_dates[-30:]), max(covid_dates[-30:]) + one_day, step=1), rotation=90)
ax.set_xticks(np.arange(min(x), max(x) + 1, step=1))


ax.margins(x=0)
plt.legend(loc=2)
plt.style.use('seaborn')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

In [21]:
def align_yaxis(ax1, v1, ax2, v2):
    """adjust ax2 ylimit so that v2 in ax2 is aligned to v1 in ax1"""
    _, y1 = ax1.transData.transform((0, v1))
    _, y2 = ax2.transData.transform((0, v2))
    inv = ax2.transData.inverted()
    _, dy = inv.transform((0, 0)) - inv.transform((0, y1-y2))
    miny, maxy = ax2.get_ylim()
    ax2.set_ylim(miny+dy, maxy+dy)
    
def autolabel(rects):
    """Attach a text label above each bar in *rects*, displaying its height."""
    for rect in rects:
        height = rect.get_height()
        ax.annotate('{}'.format(height),
        xy=(rect.get_x() + rect.get_width() / 2, height),
        xytext=(0, 0),
        textcoords="offset points",
        ha='center', va='bottom')

Maricopa County, Arizona

In [22]:
maricopa_df     = us_counties_df[us_counties_df['county'] == 'Maricopa'].iloc[-30:].sort_values(by=['date'])
maricopa_tot    = us_counties_df[us_counties_df['county'] == 'Maricopa'].iloc[-30:].groupby(['county'])['cases'].max()[0]
maricopa_deaths = us_counties_df[us_counties_df['county'] == 'Maricopa'].iloc[-30:].groupby(['county'])['deaths'].max()[0]

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 8))

x = np.arange(len(maricopa_df['date']))

ax.bar(x, maricopa_df['cases'], label='Cases', width=0.6)
ax.set(ylabel="Total Cases", title="Maricopa County COVID-19\nTotal Cases: {}\nTotal Deaths: {}".format(maricopa_tot, maricopa_deaths))
ax.set_xticklabels(np.arange(min(list(maricopa_df['date'])), max(list(maricopa_df['date'])) + datetime.timedelta(days=1), step=1), rotation=90)
ax.set_xticks(np.arange(min(x), max(x)+1, step=1))

ax2 = ax.twinx()
ax2.plot(x, maricopa_df['deaths'], label='Deaths', color='r')
ax2.set(ylabel='Total Deaths')
ax2.grid(b=False)

ax.set_yticks(np.linspace(int(ax.get_yticks()[0]), int(ax.get_yticks()[-1]), len(ax2.get_yticks())))

h1, l1 = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
h2, l2 = ax2.get_legend_handles_labels()
ax.legend(h1+h2, l1+l2, loc=2)

align_yaxis(ax, 0, ax2, 0)
ax.margins(x=0)
plt.style.use('seaborn')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Combine DataFrame containing COVID-19 data with DataFrame containing longitude and latitude data

In [29]:
us_county_data_geo_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['county', 'state', 'fips', 'cases', 'deaths', 'long', 'lat'])
us_county_data_geo_df = us_county_data_geo_df.astype({'cases': 'int64', 'deaths': 'int64'})

for idx, row in us_counties_df.groupby(['county', 'state', 'fips'])[['cases', 'deaths']].sum().reset_index(level=[0,1,2]).iterrows():
    if row['state'] != 'HI' and row['state'] != 'AK':
        us_county_data_geo_df.loc[idx] = [
            row['county'], row['state'], row['fips'], row['cases'], row['deaths'],
            counties_gdf[counties_gdf['FIPS'] == str(f"{int(row['fips']):05d}")]['LON'].max(),

n_days = 30
y = np.array(covid_data_df[covid_data_df['countriesAndTerritories'] == 'USA']['cases'][:n_days+1].diff(periods=-1)[0:-1])
x = np.array(covid_data_df[covid_data_df['countriesAndTerritories'] == 'USA']['dateRep'][:n_days])

z = np.polyfit(np.arange(len(x)), y, 1)
p = np.poly1d(z)(np.arange(len(x)))

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 8))

ax.set_title("COVID-19 US Cases Diff -1 Day (Last 30 Days)", fontsize=16)
ax.set(ylabel="Diff")
plt.xticks(rotation=90, ha='right')

ax.bar(x, y, width=0.5, label='New Cases')
ax.plot(x, p, color='r', label='Trend')

ax.legend(loc=2)

ax.margins(x=0)
plt.style.use('seaborn')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
